template:docs/core/button-group.title: Button Group
template:docs/core/button-group.text: Button Group Button group is grouping of two or more Button. Button groups arrange multiple buttons in a horizontal or vertical group. Provided some of the blueprintjs button group features as follows. Props Fill Large Minimal Vertical Align text Props Props Description alignText string Text alignment within button. By default, icons and text will be centered within the button. Passing "left" or "right" will align the button text to that side and push icon and rightIcon to either edge. Passing "center" will center the text and icons together. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. fill boolean Whether the button group should take up the full width of its container. large boolean Whether the child buttons should appear with large styling. minimal boolean Whether the button groups should appear with minimal styling. vertical boolean Whether the button group should appear with vertical styling.

template:docs/core/button.title: Button
template:docs/core/button.text: Button The Button component is used to trigger actions when user clicked. Props Minimal Active Disabled Small Large Right-Icon Fill Intent None Primary Success Warning Danger double-caret-vertical Example Icons only Props Props Description active booleanfalse If set to true, The button will display in an active state. This is equivalent to setting className='bp3-active'. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. fill boolean Whether this button should expand to fill its container. icon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render before the text. Default icon position is left iconSize number Size of icon Default icon height is 16 large boolean Whether this button should use large styles. minimal boolean Whether this button should use minimal styles. onClick Click event handler. rightIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render after the text. small boolean Whether this button should use small styles. text string Action text. type string"button" HTML type attribute of button. Common values are "clear" "button" and "submit". NOTE: only one color can be used at a time. i.e `primary/success/warning/danger` Disabled Button prevents all interaction

template:docs/core/card.title: Card
template:docs/core/card.text: Card A card is a bounded unit of UI content with a solid background color. Analytical applications User interfaces that enable people to interact smoothly with data, ask better questions, and make better decisions. Props InteractiveElevation 0 1 2 3 4 double-caret-vertical Elevation Apply an elevation value to a card to apply a drop shadow that simulates height in the UI. Five elevations are supported, from 0 to 4. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. elevation Elevation0 Controls the intensity of the drop shadow beneath the card: the higher the elevation, the higher the drop shadow. At elevation 0, no drop shadow is applied. interactive booleanfalse Whether the card should respond to user interactions. If set to true, hovering over the card will increase the card's elevation and change the mouse cursor to a pointer. Recommended when onClick is also defined. onClick (e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void Callback invoked when the card is clicked. Recommended when interactive is true.

template:docs/core/db-tree.title: Tree
template:docs/core/db-tree.text: Tree Trees display hierarchical data. Props Tree is a stateless component. Its contents are dictated by the contents argument, which is an array of Objects. The tree is multi-rooted if contents contains more than one top-level object. A variety of interaction callbacks are also exposed as args. All interaction callbacks supply a parameter nodePath, which is an array of numbers representing a node's position in the tree. Tree Node content Array objects determine the contents of the tree, appearance, and state of each node in the tree. For example, icon controls the icon displayed for the node, and isExpanded determines whether the node's children are shown. Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. hasCaret boolean Whether the caret to expand/collapse a node should be shown. If not specified, this will be true if the node has children and false otherwise. Inherited from content.hasCaret icon IconName | MaybeElement The name of a Blueprint icon (or an icon element) to render next to the node's label. id string | number A unique identifier for the node. RequiredInherited from content.id isExpanded boolean Inherited from content.isExpanded label string | Element The main label for the node. RequiredInherited from content.label onClick (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onCollapse (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLSpanElement>) => void onDoubleClick (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onExpand (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLSpanElement>) => void onMouseEnter (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void onMouseLeave (node: TreeNode<T>, e: MouseEvent<HTMLDivElement>) => void secondaryIcon string A secondary icon that is displayed at the right side of the node. Inherited from content.secondaryIcon

template:docs/core/dialog.title: Dialog Box
template:docs/core/dialog.text: Dialog Box Dialogs present content overlaid over other parts of the UI. Data integration is the seminal problem of the digital age. For over ten years, we’ve helped the world’s premier organizations rise to the challenge. Palantir Foundry radically reimagines the way enterprises interact with data by amplifying and extending the power of data integration. With Foundry, anyone can source, fuse, and transform data into any shape they desire. Business analysts become data engineers — and leaders in their organization’s data revolution. Foundry’s back end includes a suite of best-in-class data integration capabilities: data provenance, git-style versioning semantics, granular access controls, branching, transformation authoring, and more. But these powers are not limited to the back-end IT shop. In Foundry, tables, applications, reports, presentations, and spreadsheets operate as data integrations in their own right. Access controls, transformation logic, and data quality flow from original data source to intermediate analysis to presentation in real time. Every end product created in Foundry becomes a new data source that other users can build upon. And the enterprise data foundation goes where the business drives it. Start the revolution. Unleash the power of data integration with Palantir Foundry. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. isOpenDialog boolean Toggles the visibility of the overlay and its children. This prop is required because the component is controlled. Required isoutClickCloseDialog boolean Whether clicking outside the overlay element to close isEscapeToClose boolean Esc Key to close dialog box. marginTop string(ie 'px or % format') ex: marginTop='12px'. marginLeft string(ie 'px or % format') ex: marginLeft='12px'. marginRight string(ie 'px or % format') ex: marginRight='12px'. width string(ie 'px or % format') custom width ex: width='12px'. height string(ie 'px or % format') custom height ex: height='12px'. Important for dialog box Need to add <div id="destination"> <div> to main application.hbs.

template:docs/core/drawer.title: Drawer
template:docs/core/drawer.text: Drawer Drawers overlay content over existing parts of the UI and are anchored to the edge of the screen. Palantir Foundry Data integration is the seminal problem of the digital age. For over ten years, we’ve helped the world’s premier organizations rise to the challenge. Palantir Foundry radically reimagines the way enterprises interact with data by amplifying and extending the power of data integration. With Foundry, anyone can source, fuse, and transform data into any shape they desire. Business analysts become data engineers — and leaders in their organization’s data revolution. Foundry’s back end includes a suite of best-in-class data integration capabilities: data provenance, git-style versioning semantics, granular access controls, branching, transformation authoring, and more. But these powers are not limited to the back-end IT shop. In Foundry, tables, applications, reports, presentations, and spreadsheets operate as data integrations in their own right. Access controls, transformation logic, and data quality flow from original data source to intermediate analysis to presentation in real time. Every end product created in Foundry becomes a new data source that other users can build upon. And the enterprise data foundation goes where the business drives it. Start the revolution. Unleash the power of data integration with Palantir Foundry. Footer Props Size Default Small Standard Large 72% 560px Vertical Auto focus Enforce focus Has backdrop Use Portal Click outside to close Escape key to close Drawer render from left Props Use the size prop to set the size of the Drawer. This prop sets CSS width if vertical={false} (default) and height otherwise. Constants are available for common sizes: Drawer.SIZE_SMALL = 360px Drawer.SIZE_STANDARD = 50% (default) Drawer.SIZE_LARGE = 90% Props Description autoFocus booleantrue Whether the overlay should acquire application focus when it first opens. backdropClassName string CSS class names to apply to backdrop element. canEscapeKeyClose booleantrue Whether pressing the esc key should invoke onClose. canOutsideClickClose booleantrue Whether clicking outside the overlay element (either on backdrop when present or on document) should invoke onClose. class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. enforceFocus booleantrue Whether the overlay should prevent focus from leaving itself. That is, if the user attempts to focus an element outside the overlay and this prop is enabled, then the overlay will immediately bring focus back to itself. If you are nesting overlay components, either disable this prop on the "outermost" overlays or mark the nested ones usePortal={false}. hasBackdrop booleantrue Whether a container-spanning backdrop element should be rendered behind the contents. isOpen boolean Toggles the visibility of the overlay and its children. This prop is required because the component is controlled. Required onClose (event?: SyntheticEvent<HTMLElement>) => void A callback that is invoked when user interaction causes the overlay to close, such as clicking on the overlay or pressing the esc key (if enabled). Receives the event from the user's interaction, if there was an event (generally either a mouse or key event). Note that, since this component is controlled by the isOpen prop, it will not actually close itself until that args becomes false. portalClassName string Space-delimited string of class names applied to the Portal element if usePortal={true}. size number | stringsize= "50%" CSS size of the drawer. This sets width if vertical={false} (default) and height otherwise. Constants are available for common sizes: SIZE_SMALL = 360px SIZE_STANDARD = 50% SIZE_LARGE = 90% style string CSS styles to apply to the dialog. usePortal booleantrue Whether the overlay should be wrapped in a Portal, which renders its contents in a new element attached to portalContainer prop. This prop essentially determines which element is covered by the backdrop: if false, then only its parent is covered; otherwise, the entire page is covered (because the parent of the Portal is the <body> itself). Set this prop to false on nested overlays (such as Dialog or Popover) to ensure that they are rendered above their parents. vertical booleanfalse Whether the drawer should appear with vertical styling. isLeft booleanfalse Whether the drawer should place position at left side of the screen. Important for dialog box Need to add <div id="destination"> <div> to main application.hbs.The destination Id which is used for handling portal feature.

template:docs/core/icon.title: SVG Icon
template:docs/core/icon.text: SVG Icon The Icon addon which populate Blueprintjs Icons based on icon name. Props Intent None Primary Success Warning Danger double-caret-vertical Icon size chevron-up chevron-down Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. intent stringprimary It changes the color of the icon to blue. intent stringsuccess It changes the color of the icon to green, simbolises success. intent stringwarning It changes the color of the icon to yellow, warning. intent stringdanger It changes the color of the icon to red, danger. icon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render. iconSize number16 Size of the icon, in pixels. Blueprint contains 16px and 20px SVG icon images, and chooses the appropriate resolution based on this prop. Default icon size is 16 title string Description string. This string does not appear in normal browsers, but it increases accessibility. For instance, screen readers will use it for aural feedback. By default, this is set to the icon's name. color string Color of icon. This is used as the fill attribute on the <svg> image so it will override any CSS color property, including that set by intent. If this prop is omitted, icon color is inherited from surrounding text.

template:docs/core/input.title: Text inputs
template:docs/core/input.text: Text inputs The Input tag specifies an input field where the user can enter data. Props Disabled Round Readonly Large Intent None Primary Success Warning Danger double-caret-vertical Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. intent string Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,success,warning,danger,none. fill boolean Whether this input should expand to fill its container. icon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to left side of input. Default icon position is right iconSize number16 Assign Icon size. large boolean Whether this input should use large styles. Round boolean Whether this input should use round styles. readonly boolean Whether this input should readonly mode. rightIcon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render after the text. data string Input text. autofoucs boolean The cursor focus to input box pattern string Apply regex pattern for input box. ex:"[A-Za-z]{3}" maxlength number Limit the size of text inside input box. onClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Click event handler. onDoubleClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When mouse button double-clicked. onkeyUp (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When user release a key from input. onBlur (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user leaves an input field. onkeyDown (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void When a user is pressing/holding down a key. leftIconClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Left icon clicked. rightIconClick (data:string, event: MouseEvent<HTMLElement>) => void Right icon clicked. NOTE: only one color can be used at a time. i.e `primary/success/warning/danger` Disabled and readonly input prevents all interaction

template:docs/core/overflow-list.title: Overflow list
template:docs/core/overflow-list.text: Overflow list OverflowList takes a generic list of items and renders as many items as can fit inside itself. Overflowed items that do not fit are collapsed into a single element. The visible items will be recomputed when a resize is detected. The items prop accepts an array of generic objects. The required visibleItemRenderer function which determines the appearance of a visible item. The required overflowRenderer function receives all overflowed items and renders the overflow indicator. This component uses a polyfill for the proposed ResizeObserver API to efficiently detect when its dimensions change. Use the observeParents prop to watch for resizing further up in the DOM tree. Props Collapse from Start End ExampleWidth chevron-up chevron-down Props ResizeSensor requires a single DOM element child and will error otherwise. Props Description className string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. collapseFrom StringSTART(default)| END Which direction the items should collapse from: start or end of the children. This also determines whether overflowRenderer appears before (START) or after (END) the visible items. items Array of objects All items to display in the list. Items that do not fit in the container will be rendered in the overflow instead. Required minVisibleItems number0 The minimum number of visible items that should never collapse into the overflow menu, regardless of DOM dimensions. observeParents booleanfalse If true, all parent DOM elements of the container will also be observed. If changes to a parent's size is detected, the overflow will be recalculated. Only enable this prop if the overflow should be recalculated when a parent element resizes in a way that does not also cause the OverflowList to resize. style CSSProperties CSS properties to apply to the root element. tagName keyof IntrinsicElements"div" HTML tag name for the container element.

template:docs/core/panel-stack.title: Panel Stack
template:docs/core/panel-stack.text: Panel Stack PanelStack manages a stack of panels and displays only the topmost panel. Each panel appears with a header containing a "back" button to return to the previous panel. The bottom-most initialPanel cannot be closed or removed from the stack. Current stack Panels The panelList is an Array of objects. It contains {title,component} for panel-stack component. You must be add ember dyanamic component invoking code(please see above example). {component componentName} for rendering the panel list. Generating each components which avoiding cloning multiple elements. Note that each panel is only mounted when it is atop the stack and is unmounted when it is next component name applied or when a panel opens . The title will appear in the header and back button. The component is a name of your generated component name. The panelList required at leat one of the object as metioned in controller.ts. This generating different components allows the component to avoid multiple cloning elements. Note that each panel is only mounted when it is atop the stack and is unmounted when it is closed or when a panel opens above it. Props Props Description component name of generated ember component The component type to render for this panel and generated from your app. This must be a reference to the component, so it can be re-created dynamically when needed. please look at the ex. Required panelList Array of objects The panelList array is passed to the panel-stack component when it is rendered. It should contain component,title for panel rendering. Required

template:docs/core/pop-over.title: Popover
template:docs/core/pop-over.text: Popover Popover display floating content next to a target button element. Here there is a default button for popover, Popovers will render based button click. PopOver is built on top of the Popper.js Confirm deletion Are you sure you want to delete these items? You won't be able to recover them. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical May be overridden to prevent overflow Click outside to close Escape key to close Arrow Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. btnTitle string Button text of popover minimal boolean Whether this popover button should use minimal styles. active booleanfalse If set to true, the button will display in an active state. This is equivalent to setting className='bp3-active'. icon IconName Name of a Blueprint UI icon to render after the text. placement string The position (relative to the target) at which the popover should appear. deafult position is 'bottom' popOpenClickFun () => void It invoked when popover button click action occurred. arrow booleantrue Popover arrow indicator open booleanfalse External function to close popover canEscapeKeyClose booleantrue Esc Key to close popover isOutClickClose booleantrue Out side click to close popover

template:docs/core/resizesensor.title: Resize sensor
template:docs/core/resizesensor.text: Resize sensor ResizeSensor is a component that provides a "resize" event for its single DOM element child. It is a thin wrapper around ResizeObserver to provide React bindings. width is rendering @ DOM Props ResizeSensor requires a single DOM element child and will error otherwise. Props Description observeParents booleanfalse If true, all parent DOM elements of the container will also be observed for size changes. The array of entries passed to onResize will now contain an entry for each parent element up to the root of the document. Only enable this prop if a parent element resizes in a way that does not also cause the child element to resize. onResize (entries: IResizeEntry[]) => void Callback invoked when the wrapped element resizes. The entries array contains an entry for each observed element. In the default case (no observeParents), the array will contain only one element: the single child of the ResizeSensor. Note that this method is called asynchronously after a resize is detected and typically it will be called no more than once per frame. Required

template:docs/core/tag-input.title: Tag input
template:docs/core/tag-input.text: Tag input TagInput addon which is used to add new tags. You are able to add new tags with help of pressingEnter key and some of the features are mentioned as follows. Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. data Array <string> It is an array of string isCloseNotRequired boolean It remove right side cross button from tag input. placeholder string Placeholder text. disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. defaultBgcolor string Html background color for tag elements defaultFgcolor string Foreground color for tag elements. delete (index:number ) => void It return index of deleting item. save (value:string ) => void It return entered value. Tag input additional features While tag input is focused, backspace key can be used to delete a tag which is selected with a light blue border, left and right arrow key can also be used to navigate within the tags, after selection of tag backspace key will delete the tag by calling delete function with id as parameter. each tag has its own delete button which will call delete function with index as parameter. Right cross button will delete all tags.

template:docs/core/tooltip.title: Tooltip
template:docs/core/tooltip.text: Tooltip A tooltip is a lightweight popover for showing additional infromation on hover. Inline text can have this is tool tip Or, hover anywhere over this whole line. This line's tooltip is disabled. This line's tooltip is controlled by external state. Open. Available in the full range of visual intents! Props Props Description content Element | string The content that will be displayed inside of the tooltip. Required defaultIsOpen booleanfalse Initial opened state when uncontrolled. disabled booleanfalse Prevents the popover from appearing when true. intent Intent Visual intent color to apply to element. Options are primary,warning,success,danger isOpen booleanundefined Whether the popover is visible. Passing this prop puts the popover in controlled mode, where the only way to change visibility is by updating this property. If disabled={true}, this prop will be ignored, and the popover will remain closed. targetClassName string Space-delimited string of class names applied to the target element. style string CSS styles to apply to the target.

template:docs/date/date-picker.title: Date Picker
template:docs/date/date-picker.text: Date Picker A DatePicker addon shows a monthly calendar and allows the user to choose a single date. date-picker is built on top of the ember-power-calendar. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. onSelect (date: dateObject<moment>) => void date select event handler. Which will return a date object and here need to convert as you need. format string Format of date and default date format is DD/MM/YYYY.It also accept various defferent formats. isDefaultOpen boolean Default open date pop-over . date string | object Date should be '3/4/2018' format or In component.ts date:object = new Date('12/5/2018') startYear number It start the value of years select box . endYear number It limit the value of years select box . minimal boolean Minimal popover style.

template:docs/date/date-range-picker.title: Date Range Picker
template:docs/date/date-range-picker.text: Date Range Picker A DateRangePicker It shows two sequential month calendars and lets the user select a single range of days. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Shortcuts The menu on the left of the calendars provides "shortcuts" that allow users to quickly select common date ranges. The preset shortcuts can be seen in the example above. They are as follows: Past week Past month Past 3 months Past 6 months Past year Past 2 years Custom shortcuts use the following interface: Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. onSelect (date: dateObject<{start and end date}>) => void date select event handler. format string Format of date and default date format is DD/MM/YYYY isDefaultOpen boolean Default open date pop-over . range object Range is an object which contains start date and end date. ex: range: object = {start: new Date('3/1/2018'),end: new Date('3/20/2018')}; Required startYear number It start the value of years select box . endYear number It limit the value of years select box . minimal boolean Minimal popover style.

template:docs/introduction/quickstart.title: Quickstart
template:docs/introduction/quickstart.text: Quickstart Installation ember install ember-elements Styles @import "ember-elements-styles"; follow addon test style folder if other scss files required(`docs-app.scss`,`ember-cli-addon-docs.scss`)! template:docs/select/multi-select.title: MultiSelect
template:docs/select/multi-select.text: MultiSelect The MultiSelect addon which provide an option for choosing multiple items from option list. The multiple values are considered as each tags alongs with default background color and close button. You are able to change background and foreground color as mentioned below. The multiselect contain right close button which is used to remove all tags elements. Props Position when opened (placement) auto left right top bottom double-caret-vertical Minimal popover style Minimal tag style Props Props Description class string A space-delimited list of class names to pass along to a child element. style string Inline html style to parent element. data Array <string> It is an array of string which contains options for multi-select box selected Array <string> It is an array of string which contains default selected options for multi-select box placeholder string Placeholder text for multi-select box disabled boolean Whether this action is non-interactive. isDBrequired boolean It add cross icon at right corner of multi-select. isDefaultOpen boolean Default open select pop-over . onSelect (date: Array<string>) => void Selected options from multi-select box. onDelete (date: Array<string>) => void Return array of object after deletion of tag elements. minimalPopover boolean Minimal popover style. multi-select box additional features There are 6 main keys used to interact with multiselect box up & down navigation Key : navigate within the suggest box. left & right navigation Key :navigate within the selected items inside tag input. enter Key :select an item from suggest box. backspace Key : delete the search keyword and delete selected item inside tag input. NOTE: use up & down key to navigate suggest item and later enter to select. same way use left & right to navigate tags and later backspace to delete. multi select box is by default 100% in width.
